  "prompt": "Any suggested cellphone units to make me active on messanger all the time using only my data?",
  "response": "If you're looking for a cellphone that allows you to stay active on Messenger using only your mobile data, you'll want to prioritize a few key features:\n\n1. **Battery Life**: A phone with good battery life will ensure you can stay connected throughout the day.\n2. **Data Efficiency**: Look for devices that manage background data well, helping you to stay online with minimal use of your data plan.\n3. **Performance**: A phone with sufficient RAM and a reliable processor will ensure that Messenger runs smoothly.\n\nHere are some suggestions across different price ranges:\n\n### Budget Phones\n1. **Moto G Power (2023)**: Known for its excellent battery life and solid performance, the Moto G Power is great for staying connected without draining your data quickly.\n2. **Samsung Galaxy A13**: This is a budget-friendly device with good performance and battery life for daily tasks, including messaging.\n\n### Mid-Range Phones\n1. **Google Pixel 6a**: Offers a great user experience, excellent camera quality, and the stock Android experience, which can be more efficient with data usage.\n2. **Samsung Galaxy A54**: Offers an AMOLED display, decent performance, and a good battery, perfect for staying active on social apps.\n\n### High-End Phones\n1. **iPhone 14** or **iPhone 14 Pro**: iPhones are known for their optimization and efficiency. iMessage works seamlessly with Messenger, and apps generally perform well.\n2. **Samsung Galaxy S23**: High-performance smartphone with great camera capabilities, excellent battery life, and good data management.\n\n### Other Considerations\n- **Data Plan**: Regardless of the phone you choose, make sure you have a good data plan that supports your usage needs.\n- **Battery Saver Mode**: Activate this feature on your smartphone to maximize battery life when you're connected to Messenger for extended periods.\n- **Wi-Fi Settings**: When possible, connect to Wi-Fi to save on mobile data while using Messenger and other data-intensive apps.\n\nUltimately, the best choice depends on your budget and preferences. Be sure to check reviews and compare specifications before making a final decision!",
